         <notesStmt>
            <note>Folio 1r contain an imperfect list of poetical pieces, but not all the piyuṭim enumerated are contained in the present volume.The last two folios (folios 89-90) are from another manuscript.
								Mosheh Yehudah: inscribed with his name in Hebrew, next to it illegible signature in Latin letters with the same ink (lower margin, folio 81v).

								Emanuel de Miliyat?: inscribed with his name (folio 85v).</note>
