                        <foliation>Quire numbering in upper right corner; quires viii and ix are equally numbered as 8. </foliation>
                        <collation>
                           <p>
									11 quires: i10 (folios 1-10), ii8 (folios 11-18), iii8-1 (folios 19-26), iv8 (folios 27-34), v10 (folios 35-44), vi12-2 (folios 45-54), vii8 (folios 55-62), viii8-2 (folios 63-68), ix8 (folios 69-76), x8 (folios 77-84 ), xi6 (folios 85-90). 
									Catchwords at the end of the quires, often decorated.
								</p>
                        </collation>
                     </supportDesc>
                     <layoutDesc>
                        <layout>
                           <p>Columns: 1;
                                                  ruled lines: 22;
                                                  written lines: 21; Uniform layout.Visible pricking and hard-point ruling.Initial words written in larger characters.Hair side and flesh side are distinguishable.Numerous marginal notes by various hands.Deleted paragraphs (erasure of censor?) e.g., folios 36r, 78v.</p>
                        </layout>
                     </layoutDesc>
                  </objectDesc>
                  <scriptDesc>
                     <scriptNote>Ashkenazi square and semi-cursive script, partially punctuated, with a number of notes in Italian and other semi-cursive and cursive scripts. Ḥayim: the word ḥayim is decorated (e.g. folios 2v, 3v, 8r, 19v, 44r, 49r, 51v, 87v). </scriptNote>
                  </scriptDesc>
